<br>
But other than that....lets get serious here.  There are very few world leaders that have had to deal with the amount of Crapola that Bush has had to deal with since he took office.  After 911, I am surprised we have an economy at all...let alone one that is starting to grow again.  Most people can not contemplate the immense ammount of money that went through the twin towers on a daily basis.....and at each stop in teh money flow...an american company got a slice.  Suddenly on 911 this income stopped....which further hurt an allready struggleing economy..which was on the rebound at the time(BTW Bush predicted teh economic Downturn if you remember correctly).  So what'd we do?  We found those responsible and attacked.  Wether you beleive in it or not ... that was the only way to disrupt the terrist activity.  You will NEVER stop ALL terrorism....but if you can keep them disorganized....kill their infrastructure you Greatly lower the chances that an operation so BIG so Complicated can ever happen again.  Sure...we have not found bin laden yet....but only one thing is harder to find than a Desert Rat .... and that's a Very Weathy and well connected Desert Rat.  We will eventually get him, and when we do I'd very much like to be the person that throw's the switch when he fries......heck, it'd be worth it to turn the juice up slowly....maybe over a coarse of days... to get more Twitch factor out of the whole ordeal......<br>
<br>
Iraq.  A very contraversial decision.  No on can know how this will turn out...we all hope for the best.   This was a message...plain and simple.  After 911, President Bush said that we would go after ANYONE supporting terrorist activity preemptively to ensure our security.   Iraq was the proof that we meant what we said.  Noone can honestly say the world isn't safer with Saddam out of power.  Personally I beleive that the US is incredibly more safe with him out of power.   I think it is very naive to beleive that saddam wasn't aiding terrorists.  Lets look at some facts.  <br>
<br>
1) Saddam HATES the United States with every fiber of his being.  <br>
<br>
2)He is one of the wealthiest men in teh world.  <br>
<br>
3)He is in the middle East with easy access to MANY of the terrorist groups you hear of all the time on the news.<br>
<br>
4) Saddam Prefer's to deal in cash....as it isn't NEARLY as traceable. <br>
<br>
5) Saddam is a certifiable Homicidal Maniac which does NOT value his own peoples lives.....let alone lives that are shattered elsewhere in the world because of terrorist activity. <br>
<br>
Now, which of these facts DON'T ncourage the beleif that he would fund terrorism?  Heck I bet he actively sought out terrorist groups to give moeny too... <br>
<br>
True, he is still a very rich man that can cause trouble for the USA with even more reason to hate us now..... but now he has to hide like a common Criminal,.....and not behind a army and a nation.  He is NOT free to act as he was before because he is on teh run...sometimes outditancing our forces by mere hours.  Saddam Husein will be caught.  He is a creature of certain comfort......he can't live in a cave for month's on end like Bin Laden, and that will be his undoing.<br>
<br>
SO to recap, look at all the crapola Bush has had to deal with unexpectedly during his presidency.   Is it HIS fault the showdown with terrorists happen to occur during his watch?  No.  Howelse would YOU have handled the terrorist problem?  The fact is teh decision to take the fight to them(i.e. the terrorists) is what has kept us from getting bitch slapped left and right by these SOB's.  They had more to come folks....they had more terrorist acts in teh US planned.....but we interrupted thier operations.  We might have another big terrorist attack tomorrow....and if we do then I will mourn like everyone esle....but I WON'T point an accusing finger to Bush and scream that he hasn't done enough, or has been WRONG in his actions.  Because if we hadn't taken the steps that we have, then we'd be used to getting attcked by now.  <br>
<br>
Bush gets my vote in '04.<br>
