<br>
You act like he is the first president to have this problem.  Have you ever watched Saturday Night Live?  Numerous comedians have made what passes for entire careers by finding some idiosyncrasy of the sitting president and exploiting it to the fullest.  This has been done to every single president since I have been alive, and since I neither worship satan or consider myself the center of the universe, I would imagine it happened before then too.  I still call Sadaam, Sadam like Sr. because I find it funny as hell.  I know its incorrect just like I imagine Sr. did, but its funny and I like it.  <br>
<br>
Have you ever seen the other leaders of the world speak in public?  There are some serious freaks out there.  Half the time the Russian leader of the day can barely stand up without putting down the vodka bottle to hold himself up.  The canadian PM doesnt know his ass from a hole in the ground but stays in office by saying cool shit like &quot;Hey I think Im going to fire up a blunt as soon as I retire.&quot;  Or the fued going on between Germany and Spain(or is it Italy) because their leaders continue to say dumb ass shit to the media.  And dont even start on the middle eastern/asian leaders where knock down drag fights in what passes for their congress are a regular occurance.<br>
<br>
When ever you examine ever single detail of anyones life under a microscope you are going to find some stupid shit that they have done/still do.  Given our past 15 or so presidents this is magnified in that office.  GW does stupid shit, Slick Willy did stupid shit, Sr. did stupid shit.  Hell, they are even about to fillet Reagan in a made for tv movie and while he was in office, he could do no wrong unless you were homosexual.  Carter was the biggest joke ever while he was in office, and now people are trying to throw Nobel Peace prizes at him and some are saying upon closer examination of his accomplishments while president, he might even be one of the top 5 presidents EVER.  Jimmy PEANUT FUCKING FARMER Carter.<br>
<br>
Bottomline is, Bush is the best of what is out there no matter how sad of a statement that is.  If the election was tomorrow he would win; whether it was for the next term or a rerun of the last election.  He would win huge.  And unless the democrats find someone real to run against him, he will stilll win huge when time for the vote actually rolls around.  All of the people that would make really good presidents are either making too much money in the private sector to take the pay cut or are on the opposite end of the spectrum and have too little money/influence to make a run at the office.  <br>
<br>
