<br>
As for the list of Bush's accomplishments, lets think about the prior president:<br>
<br>
1. Clinton presided over a dot com boom that was nothing more than a new incarnation of a catalog. Actually making money on the internet was less important than offering an IPO. Style over substance finally gave out and the economic growth he prided himself for creating finally burst because it wasn't real, leaving a mess for the next president to clean up because Bill was a sitting duck. <br>
<br>
2. The financial crisis many states, and most notably California, are in is a direct result of the dot com bust. Politicians aren't as smart as farmers. Farmers understand the concept of a 'bumper' crop, politicians on the other hand think taxes 'will always roll in at this rate'. <br>
<br>
3. Enron did not begin its corporate fraud January 2000, when GWB took office as president. Worldcom/MCI and others were also blasted for book-cooking that dated back for years. If people can clain that GWB is somehow afforded tertiary blame for the greatest number of bankruptcies and foreclosures then in the same light Bill Clinton bears the same blame for the corruption in corporate America. <br>
<br>
4. Both Clinton and Gore received 'shady' campaign contributions from Chineese ties. Strangely enough on the Clinton/Gore watch key missile technologies were leaked to the Chineese. <br>
<br>
5. Clinton had first shot at the terrorists. The World Trade Center was attacked TWICE!!! Had Clinton been doing his job instead of getting blowjobs from fat interns perhaps GWB wouldn't have had to go to the UN and say &quot;If you don't say its ok for The U.S. of A. to protect itself, then fuck off. I don't need you.&quot;<br>
<br>
6. THE US DID NOT ACT UNILATERALY IN ATTACKING IRAQ. We had at least one country aiding us, (actually it was more, but by definition unilateraly means acting alone, so all I need is one country to invalidate this notion.)<br>
